{
  "stem": "2067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On May 10, 1940, the Germans invaded Holland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I want to mention that from the day that the war broke out, 1st September-- 3rd of September 1939, until that time, I tried desperately to obtain any kind of visa.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The American visa was out of the question.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They told us we would have to wait maybe six years before-- before our quota number would be reached.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I tried to-- I went to South American consul, since I spoke fluent Spanish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was inexperienced.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't understand at that time that you had to bribe them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had to give money to a consul of Chile or to Paraguay or to Peru or wherever, these small Latin American countries, to get a visa.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's why I didn't succeed-- fortunately, didn't succeed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now the war was on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The year 1940 was rather quiet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Apparently, the Germans, unlike in countries in Eastern Europe, didn't want to show the Western-- to the Western European countries, especially in Holland, which they considered an Aryan country, that they were using inhuman and brutal, murderous methods against Jews.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So nothing much happened in 1940.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But '41 brought a big change.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first anti-Jewish decrees came off, and from then on, one after the other.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It started out with creating a ghetto in Amsterdam, the main Jewish city in Holland.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The ghetto was the part where Rembrandt had lived, a 500-year-old downtown area of Amsterdam, where mainly Jewish and Jewish businesses and stores were.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A ghetto was erected there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And anyone who entered-- Gentiles were forced to leave that area and Jews who entered that area had to show an identity card.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
